Thursday, October 13, 1994

MERIT DOCKET

94-2154. Daniels v. Nunez.

In Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a emergency complaint for a writ of prohibition and was considered in a manner prescribed by law. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the writ of prohibition be, and the same is hereby, denied.

Moyer, C.J., A.W. Sweeney, Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney and Pfeifer, JJ., concur.
